President Obama announced his intent to nominate three individuals to key administration posts. Katherine G. Hammack was nominated for Assistant Secretary of the Army (Installations and Environment) at the Department of Defense. She has over 25 years of experience in energy and sustainability and is currently a leader in Ernst & Young's Climate Change and Sustainability Services. Theodore Sedgwick was nominated for Ambassador to the Slovak Republic at the Department of State. He is a business executive with experience in publishing and timber industries. Dennis P. Walsh was nominated for Chairman of the Special Panel on Appeals. He is currently the Deputy General Counsel at the Federal Labor Relations Authority and has previously served as a Member of the National Labor Relations Board.